IMO, this is an artist riding the crest of a creative tidal wave that he feels before the rest of us.  He knew he was more than a one hit wonder (Space Oddity), had just switched gears from the Man who Sold the World, and banged out Hunky Dory, had convinced Mick Ronson to come back (the “Keith” to Bowie’s “Mick”), knew he had Ziggy on the come. The Spiders were his next phase and he knew he could switch to whatever he wanted, when he wanted, and succeed.

But, to me, the the Bowie/Ronson collaboration was the pinnacle, and changed Rock forever.

